The paper deals with the problem of measuring the impact of DoS attacks in real-time using Twitter data. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as the paper deals with mitigating the effects of DoS attacks. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as Latent Dirichlet Allocation and symmetric Kullback-Leibler divergence to analyze the Twitter data, which falls under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with analyzing large amounts of data, which falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SD).
